1
00:02:06,345 --> 00:02:09,105
You've had him follow me
since we separated.

2
00:02:09,864 --> 00:02:11,105
Are you a psychopath?

3
00:02:11,184 --> 00:02:12,305
Why are you doing this?

4
00:02:12,904 --> 00:02:16,265
I'm doing all this because I love you.

5
00:02:16,344 --> 00:02:19,305
If I can't be happy, then no one will be.

6
00:02:19,385 --> 00:02:21,064
If I wasn't indecisive,

7
00:02:22,865 --> 00:02:24,064
if I had been firm…

8
00:02:25,305 --> 00:02:28,105
I wouldn't have made the wrong choice.

9
00:02:28,184 --> 00:02:29,785
She didn't really love him.

10
00:02:29,865 --> 00:02:32,064
I'm just a product of their mistake.

11
00:02:33,105 --> 00:02:34,464
Am I supposed to give up

12
00:02:34,545 --> 00:02:36,505
and be a coward like you?

13
00:02:37,025 --> 00:02:39,064
And behave immorally like you?

14
00:02:39,624 --> 00:02:41,505
-I can't do it.
-Tarn!

15
00:02:43,145 --> 00:02:45,105
I already have plenty of friends.

16
00:02:46,344 --> 00:02:47,265
But now,

17
00:02:47,985 --> 00:02:49,344
I want you.

18
00:04:03,784 --> 00:04:05,105
Happy birthday, Nut.

19
00:04:19,824 --> 00:04:21,665
We made you a cake.

20
00:04:57,225 --> 00:04:59,505
What decoration do you want
on your cake this year?

21
00:05:01,824 --> 00:05:03,824
I want a rainbow.

22
00:05:05,824 --> 00:05:07,824
With these colors please, Mom.

23
00:05:08,385 --> 00:05:10,185
That looks hard.

24
00:05:11,185 --> 00:05:12,945
You need to help me then.

25
00:05:13,024 --> 00:05:14,385
All right.

26
00:05:14,465 --> 00:05:17,425
You are a boy.
You shouldn't like pastel rainbows.

27
00:05:17,985 --> 00:05:19,065
It's silly.

28
00:05:29,225 --> 00:05:31,704
You should teach him right from wrong.

29
00:05:32,185 --> 00:05:34,024
Don't spoil him.

30
00:06:03,144 --> 00:06:04,505
Nut.

31
00:06:05,345 --> 00:06:06,865
How about we pick a new pattern?

32
00:06:06,945 --> 00:06:08,385
How about an ocean?

33
00:07:08,625 --> 00:07:09,665
Nut.

34
00:07:10,144 --> 00:07:13,065
What pattern would you like
on your birthday cake?

35
00:07:13,144 --> 00:07:14,305
Anything is fine, Mom.

36
00:07:17,584 --> 00:07:19,745
Can you put a piece in a box for me?

37
00:07:20,264 --> 00:07:22,225
I want my friend to try it.

38
00:07:22,305 --> 00:07:23,344
Sure.

39
00:07:26,785 --> 00:07:28,505
Look at the activities you do.

40
00:07:30,024 --> 00:07:32,305
Don't you know how to do
any manly activities?

41
00:07:47,344 --> 00:07:49,425
It might be almost 20 years late.

42
00:07:51,945 --> 00:07:53,704
But I still want to do this for you.

43
00:07:56,985 --> 00:07:59,344
I may have made mistakes in the past.

44
00:08:02,464 --> 00:08:04,425
But please know that…

45
00:08:07,065 --> 00:08:09,464
you are not one of them.

46
00:08:12,704 --> 00:08:14,704
You are my gift.

47
00:08:17,464 --> 00:08:19,105
Happy birthday.

48
00:08:49,665 --> 00:08:51,385
I'm not too late, am I?

49
00:08:52,424 --> 00:08:54,225
Happy birthday, Nut.

50
00:09:00,064 --> 00:09:01,865
I wish you happiness.

51
00:09:12,105 --> 00:09:14,105
Thank you.

52
00:09:14,184 --> 00:09:15,585
-Sure.
-Let's go inside.

53
00:09:19,665 --> 00:09:21,665
It might seem a little old,

54
00:09:21,745 --> 00:09:23,944
but doesn't it look like
the teddy bear you lost?

55
00:09:24,865 --> 00:09:26,745
Yes, it really does.

56
00:09:44,424 --> 00:09:46,424
I didn't think I would find a teddy bear

57
00:09:46,505 --> 00:09:48,025
similar to your last one.

58
00:09:49,905 --> 00:09:51,225
I was lucky, I guess.

59
00:10:06,745 --> 00:10:08,225
Do you know

60
00:10:09,225 --> 00:10:11,625
that I worked really hard to find it?

61
00:10:13,665 --> 00:10:15,665
I put in a lot of effort.

62
00:10:18,465 --> 00:10:20,465
The same goes for the feelings

63
00:10:21,145 --> 00:10:22,944
that I have for you.

64
00:10:30,265 --> 00:10:31,985
I know

65
00:10:32,064 --> 00:10:34,145
that we haven't known
each other for so long.

66
00:10:36,184 --> 00:10:37,865
It might be too early

67
00:10:38,385 --> 00:10:40,385
for me to be saying this.

68
00:10:42,625 --> 00:10:45,585
But I can't let any more time pass by.

69
00:10:49,184 --> 00:10:51,184
On my first day at work,

70
00:10:52,064 --> 00:10:54,544
you scolded those drunks for me.

71
00:10:56,064 --> 00:10:57,985
You looked so damn cool.

72
00:10:59,424 --> 00:11:01,985
I became your fan after that day.

73
00:11:03,505 --> 00:11:05,145
Although you pretended not to care,

74
00:11:05,665 --> 00:11:07,184
ignored me,

75
00:11:07,265 --> 00:11:09,265
and had that confused look on your face,

76
00:11:11,544 --> 00:11:13,544
your heart was filled with warmth

77
00:11:15,585 --> 00:11:18,665
and I couldn't stop myself
from falling for you.

78
00:11:24,265 --> 00:11:25,304
I didn't know

79
00:11:25,385 --> 00:11:28,585
the best way to confess my feelings,

80
00:11:29,745 --> 00:11:32,625
so I bought you this special gift.

81
00:11:39,345 --> 00:11:40,865
Thank you so much

82
00:11:41,944 --> 00:11:43,265
for this special gift, Prib.

83
00:11:46,665 --> 00:11:50,465
However, no matter how similar
this teddy bear is to my old one,

84
00:11:51,424 --> 00:11:53,345
I can't accept it.

85
00:12:00,145 --> 00:12:01,265
Prib.

86
00:12:04,304 --> 00:12:06,345
You know that I don't feel the same way.

87
00:12:14,184 --> 00:12:15,705
I understand.

88
00:12:18,985 --> 00:12:20,345
I know

89
00:12:20,865 --> 00:12:23,265
that I can't change your mind.

90
00:12:27,585 --> 00:12:29,585
I just wanted to show you

91
00:12:30,905 --> 00:12:32,385
how serious I am about you.

92
00:12:38,225 --> 00:12:39,505
It's okay

93
00:12:39,585 --> 00:12:40,824
if you feel differently.

94
00:12:48,184 --> 00:12:49,625
It's okay

95
00:12:52,345 --> 00:12:53,544
if you don't love me.

96
00:12:56,865 --> 00:12:58,064
I'm okay.

97
00:13:02,304 --> 00:13:03,385
Prib.

98
00:13:07,704 --> 00:13:10,025
I came to wish you a happy birthday.

99
00:13:16,184 --> 00:13:18,505
I wish you all the happiness in the world.

100
00:13:32,745 --> 00:13:34,865
Even though
I can't be that someone for you,

101
00:13:36,385 --> 00:13:37,465
-we can still--
-Stop.

102
00:13:43,225 --> 00:13:46,064
I know what you are going to say.

103
00:13:55,704 --> 00:13:57,064
You're going to say

104
00:13:57,145 --> 00:13:59,265
that I can be your sister, right?

105
00:14:02,865 --> 00:14:03,704
Can you?

106
00:14:19,465 --> 00:14:21,225
I'm not ready right now.

107
00:14:23,584 --> 00:14:26,145
But I will be.

108
00:15:07,505 --> 00:15:08,704
Prib.

109
00:15:14,064 --> 00:15:15,064
Shall we go home?

110
00:15:16,745 --> 00:15:17,944
It's okay.

111
00:15:19,105 --> 00:15:20,544
I got here on my own.

112
00:15:20,625 --> 00:15:22,385
I can go home alone as well.

113
00:15:25,025 --> 00:15:25,905
I'll be all right.

114
00:15:37,544 --> 00:15:38,745
Are you all right?

115
00:15:39,424 --> 00:15:40,345
Yes.

116
00:15:40,865 --> 00:15:42,465
I'm okay.

117
00:15:46,625 --> 00:15:48,105
You're not okay.

118
00:15:48,184 --> 00:15:50,385
You're eating barbecue with a teddy bear.

119
00:15:50,944 --> 00:15:52,824
Are you sure you're okay? Are you?

120
00:15:56,464 --> 00:15:58,345
I'm hungry.

121
00:15:59,265 --> 00:16:01,424
And I'm sad.

122
00:16:08,184 --> 00:16:09,704
I saw her holding the teddy bear

123
00:16:09,785 --> 00:16:11,265
and tripping over

124
00:16:11,345 --> 00:16:13,105
in front of the restaurant,

125
00:16:13,184 --> 00:16:14,584
so I called you.

126
00:16:19,184 --> 00:16:20,025
Prib.

127
00:16:20,105 --> 00:16:22,704
What are you going to do
with that teddy bear?

128
00:16:23,865 --> 00:16:26,105
I'm going to donate it.

129
00:16:27,304 --> 00:16:28,944
Nut doesn't want it.

130
00:16:30,464 --> 00:16:33,625
But I'm sure somebody
will want it one day.

131
00:16:35,704 --> 00:16:37,424
All right then.

132
00:16:37,944 --> 00:16:40,025
Cheer up. Somebody will want you
one day too.

133
00:16:42,184 --> 00:16:43,665
Right?

134
00:16:43,745 --> 00:16:46,304
I'm beautiful, kind, and cute.

135
00:16:46,385 --> 00:16:48,105
Plus, I've got time for him.

136
00:16:48,184 --> 00:16:50,385
How can nobody want me?

137
00:16:55,665 --> 00:16:57,424
Why am I so unlucky?

138
00:16:57,505 --> 00:17:00,785
I always end up in the friend zone.

139
00:17:05,065 --> 00:17:08,224
Prib, your soulmate might be a foreigner.

140
00:17:09,504 --> 00:17:11,545
A foreign creature from another world.

141
00:17:16,704 --> 00:17:18,184
Being his friend

142
00:17:19,065 --> 00:17:20,984
is better than being a stranger.

143
00:17:21,865 --> 00:17:22,944
That's right.

144
00:17:23,665 --> 00:17:25,944
You are better off as his friend.

145
00:17:26,024 --> 00:17:27,545
The bond will last longer.

146
00:17:29,744 --> 00:17:31,905
Are you comforting me or rubbing it in?

147
00:17:33,345 --> 00:17:34,744
I'm comforting you.

148
00:17:35,425 --> 00:17:36,385
I love you.

149
00:17:37,705 --> 00:17:38,665
Eat this.

150
00:17:38,744 --> 00:17:39,825
It will keep you quiet.

151
00:17:40,744 --> 00:17:41,984
It's hot.

152
00:17:44,145 --> 00:17:45,705
I love you too, mister.

153
00:17:46,825 --> 00:17:47,905
Wait, what?

154
00:17:49,024 --> 00:17:50,865
What a sneaky little bastard.

155
00:17:58,345 --> 00:17:59,264
Stop.

156
00:18:00,145 --> 00:18:01,345
You can drink,

157
00:18:01,425 --> 00:18:03,065
but don't throw up like last time.

158
00:18:56,665 --> 00:18:58,305
What are you doing, Nut?

159
00:19:00,905 --> 00:19:01,744
Well…

160
00:19:02,225 --> 00:19:04,065
I'm recording this moment like you do.

161
00:19:05,105 --> 00:19:06,225
You're recording it?

162
00:19:06,305 --> 00:19:07,585
Then I should be in it too.

163
00:19:23,945 --> 00:19:24,945
Thank you

164
00:19:25,504 --> 00:19:27,665
for throwing me a birthday party.

165
00:19:29,425 --> 00:19:30,665
Do you like it?

166
00:19:32,425 --> 00:19:33,264
Yes.

167
00:19:34,545 --> 00:19:35,705
Do you like the party

168
00:19:36,345 --> 00:19:37,625
or me?

169
00:19:40,264 --> 00:19:41,665
What a cheap shot.

170
00:19:43,425 --> 00:19:44,705
Well…

171
00:19:45,465 --> 00:19:46,625
I like both of them.

172
00:19:49,744 --> 00:19:51,264
What about the teddy bear?

173
00:19:52,065 --> 00:19:53,465
Did you not like it?

174
00:19:54,784 --> 00:19:55,825
No.

175
00:19:56,744 --> 00:19:58,225
It kind of freaked me out.

176
00:19:59,705 --> 00:20:01,425
How could they look so similar?

177
00:20:03,145 --> 00:20:04,465
But the truth is

178
00:20:05,465 --> 00:20:06,665
their colors,

179
00:20:07,705 --> 00:20:09,105
eyes,

180
00:20:10,225 --> 00:20:11,665
and smells were different.

181
00:20:14,984 --> 00:20:16,385
And most importantly,

182
00:20:17,145 --> 00:20:18,504
it wasn't as warm to hug.

183
00:20:22,465 --> 00:20:24,185
That's why you didn't like it.

184
00:20:25,865 --> 00:20:26,784
Yes.

185
00:20:28,264 --> 00:20:30,945
Despite their similarities,

186
00:20:33,465 --> 00:20:35,145
the teddy bear is irreplaceable.

187
00:20:38,545 --> 00:20:39,784
What if

188
00:20:41,385 --> 00:20:42,744
it's me?

189
00:20:43,744 --> 00:20:45,905
Am I good enough
to replace your teddy bear?

190
00:20:50,585 --> 00:20:52,185
You are you.

191
00:20:53,504 --> 00:20:55,225
You can't replace anyone.

192
00:20:57,465 --> 00:20:59,425
When you asked me what I wanted

193
00:20:59,504 --> 00:21:01,585
for my birthday

194
00:21:02,465 --> 00:21:03,905
and I said nothing,

195
00:21:08,465 --> 00:21:09,905
that's because

196
00:21:12,024 --> 00:21:13,585
I already have you.

197
00:21:19,504 --> 00:21:21,185
Stay by my side…

198
00:21:24,425 --> 00:21:25,705
and don't go anywhere.

199
00:21:49,705 --> 00:21:51,185
What did you do, Tofu?

200
00:21:52,225 --> 00:21:54,784
It's how adults make promises.

201
00:21:56,105 --> 00:21:57,425
I promise

202
00:21:57,984 --> 00:21:59,744
to be with you forever.

203
00:22:03,825 --> 00:22:04,665
In that case…

204
00:22:06,385 --> 00:22:07,465
please stay

205
00:22:10,305 --> 00:22:11,585
with me tonight.

206
00:22:37,345 --> 00:22:39,865
What a wonderful night.

207
00:22:40,905 --> 00:22:43,024
I've become Nut's special someone.

208
00:22:43,984 --> 00:22:47,105
And I'm going back to Nut's room.

209
00:23:57,185 --> 00:23:58,225
Hey.

210
00:23:59,905 --> 00:24:01,145
You weren't sleeping.

211
00:24:01,625 --> 00:24:03,145
I was curious to see

212
00:24:03,225 --> 00:24:04,425
what you were going to do.

213
00:24:05,585 --> 00:24:07,185
Why didn't you wake me up?

214
00:24:10,544 --> 00:24:11,465
Well…

215
00:24:12,744 --> 00:24:14,504
I wanted to stay like this.

216
00:24:19,705 --> 00:24:20,625
Thank you

217
00:24:22,264 --> 00:24:23,585
for coming here.

218
00:24:25,024 --> 00:24:26,705
Thank you for caring about me.

219
00:24:28,865 --> 00:24:30,585
Thank you for everything.

220
00:24:33,625 --> 00:24:34,865
Without you,

221
00:24:36,385 --> 00:24:38,585
I'm not sure
if I would have gotten through it.

222
00:24:41,665 --> 00:24:43,145
Your mom said

223
00:24:44,465 --> 00:24:46,665
love isn't about doing
something for someone.

224
00:24:48,264 --> 00:24:50,744
It's about putting your heart into it.

225
00:24:53,665 --> 00:24:55,625
My heart is all yours.

226
00:24:59,465 --> 00:25:01,345
Yes, I know.

227
00:25:10,385 --> 00:25:12,264
I wish we could stay this way forever.

228
00:25:16,024 --> 00:25:17,665
You smell nice.

229
00:25:18,264 --> 00:25:19,425
So does your hair.

230
00:25:39,504 --> 00:25:40,905
But I think

231
00:25:42,865 --> 00:25:44,024
you stink.

232
00:25:46,665 --> 00:25:47,744
It's your hair.

233
00:25:49,065 --> 00:25:50,065
Smell it.

234
00:25:55,705 --> 00:25:57,225
It doesn't stink.

235
00:25:57,304 --> 00:25:58,385
It stinks.

236
00:26:02,465 --> 00:26:03,705
It doesn't.

237
00:26:03,784 --> 00:26:05,145
Trust me. It stinks.

238
00:26:05,825 --> 00:26:08,065
Go take a shower.

239
00:26:11,225 --> 00:26:12,544
I'll wash your hair for you.

240
00:27:10,465 --> 00:27:11,665
Kuenchai.

241
00:27:11,744 --> 00:27:12,984
Kuenchai.

242
00:27:13,065 --> 00:27:14,544
Kuenchai, come eat.

243
00:27:26,905 --> 00:27:27,905
I'm leaving, Mom.

244
00:27:28,625 --> 00:27:29,544
Okay.

245
00:27:32,865 --> 00:27:33,705
I'm leaving.

246
00:27:34,744 --> 00:27:36,264
Did you forget something?

247
00:27:44,065 --> 00:27:44,945
What?

248
00:27:46,905 --> 00:27:48,185
Your lunchbox.

249
00:28:12,385 --> 00:28:13,385
Thank you.

250
00:28:17,345 --> 00:28:18,665
I'll get going then.

251
00:28:26,705 --> 00:28:27,865
I realized

252
00:28:28,585 --> 00:28:30,744
why people were yearning for love.

253
00:28:31,544 --> 00:28:33,825
Love is a wonderful thing.

254
00:28:34,945 --> 00:28:38,064
It's so wonderful that I don't want
to be a teddy bear again.

255
00:29:13,665 --> 00:29:15,784
Prib, are you heartbroken again?

256
00:29:15,865 --> 00:29:17,544
You're drawing men.

257
00:29:18,024 --> 00:29:20,625
Yes, I'm permanently heartbroken.

258
00:29:22,945 --> 00:29:25,345
Did you confess your feelings to that guy?

259
00:29:25,825 --> 00:29:28,264
Yes, we talked it out.

260
00:29:30,264 --> 00:29:31,385
Are you sad?

261
00:29:32,865 --> 00:29:34,744
It's no use being sad.

262
00:29:34,825 --> 00:29:36,825
I better put my time into something else.

263
00:29:36,905 --> 00:29:38,865
I have an important mission.

264
00:29:38,945 --> 00:29:40,585
What are you talking about?

265
00:29:44,145 --> 00:29:46,984
I'm going to find that person for Tarn.

266
00:29:48,625 --> 00:29:49,945
Perhaps,

267
00:29:50,585 --> 00:29:52,705
I was born for this.

268
00:29:55,345 --> 00:29:56,544
You…

269
00:30:09,665 --> 00:30:11,425
Kuenchai, come and eat.

270
00:30:15,945 --> 00:30:17,544
You already gave him his food.

271
00:30:19,665 --> 00:30:20,984
Did I?

272
00:30:27,024 --> 00:30:28,385
When?

273
00:31:42,504 --> 00:31:43,905
What's wrong, Tofu?

274
00:31:43,984 --> 00:31:46,665
You were happy this morning.

275
00:31:48,744 --> 00:31:49,865
It's Mrs. Na.

276
00:31:51,425 --> 00:31:52,705
Lately,

277
00:31:52,784 --> 00:31:54,465
she has been forgetful.

278
00:31:55,345 --> 00:31:57,625
She forgot that she had fed Kuenchai
this morning.

279
00:31:58,145 --> 00:31:59,544
And this book,

280
00:32:00,064 --> 00:32:01,984
she has been reading the same page.

281
00:32:02,625 --> 00:32:07,945
Maybe it's…

282
00:32:08,024 --> 00:32:12,425
The medicine makes her…

283
00:32:13,024 --> 00:32:14,385
Is everyone okay?

284
00:32:14,465 --> 00:32:15,304
Well…

285
00:32:16,264 --> 00:32:17,225
