you're doing laundry.

570
00:56:10,185 --> 00:56:11,705
I can't let you do it alone.

571
00:56:13,545 --> 00:56:14,745
We used it together,

572
00:56:15,305 --> 00:56:16,944
so let's wash it together.

573
00:56:29,785 --> 00:56:31,065
Press the button.

574
00:56:35,625 --> 00:56:38,105
You don't even know how to do laundry.

575
00:56:52,065 --> 00:56:52,944
I'm sorry.

576
00:56:53,025 --> 00:56:56,225
-You're sorry?
-Nut.

577
00:56:56,825 --> 00:56:58,145
-Nut.
-Tofu.

578
00:56:58,225 --> 00:56:59,424
Tofu.

579
00:57:38,504 --> 00:57:39,825
I have to shower again.

580
00:57:41,065 --> 00:57:44,065
Ask Kuenchai who started the fight.

581
00:57:49,745 --> 00:57:52,024
-Yes, Juea.
-I need your advice.

582
00:57:53,785 --> 00:57:56,305
Don't ask questions. Come now.

583
00:57:56,864 --> 00:57:57,944
All right.

584
00:57:59,745 --> 00:58:01,024
I'm going to the office.

585
00:58:01,585 --> 00:58:02,705
Okay.

586
00:58:10,504 --> 00:58:12,305
Nut is so cute.

587
00:58:17,904 --> 00:58:19,065
Mr. Rocking Chair.

588
00:58:21,424 --> 00:58:22,424
Ms. Sofa.

589
00:58:23,864 --> 00:58:24,785
Ms. Phone.

590
00:58:25,424 --> 00:58:26,504
Are you still sleeping?

591
00:58:26,585 --> 00:58:27,904
I'm so sleepy.

592
00:58:27,984 --> 00:58:29,944
I don't want to get up.

593
00:58:33,384 --> 00:58:34,864
Ms. Phone.

594
00:58:38,424 --> 00:58:39,585
Ms. Phone.

595
00:58:41,265 --> 00:58:42,384
What are you doing?

596
00:58:45,545 --> 00:58:47,345
It went off.

597
00:58:47,424 --> 00:58:48,864
I was going to charge it.

598
00:58:48,944 --> 00:58:52,345
I've been trying to charge it
since yesterday, but it won't work.

599
00:58:53,065 --> 00:58:54,545
I guess it's broken.

600
00:58:58,345 --> 00:58:59,265
Kuenchai.

601
00:58:59,984 --> 00:59:01,305
He's digging again.

602
00:59:06,464 --> 00:59:07,625
Is it possible

603
00:59:08,384 --> 00:59:10,024
that Ms. Phone fell asleep too?

604
00:59:11,745 --> 00:59:12,864
What about me?

605
00:59:14,464 --> 00:59:16,024
How much time do I have left?

606
00:59:24,625 --> 00:59:27,705
Kids are so rude these days.

607
00:59:29,745 --> 00:59:30,665
Oh, my…

608
00:59:30,745 --> 00:59:33,065
There must be a thunderstorm.

609
00:59:33,145 --> 00:59:37,105
My niece is working early in the morn…

610
00:59:38,265 --> 00:59:39,345
You're not working.

611
00:59:39,904 --> 00:59:41,504
What are you looking at?

612
00:59:43,185 --> 00:59:45,825
Doesn't the guy with the book

613
00:59:45,904 --> 00:59:47,225
seem familiar to you?

614
00:59:50,145 --> 00:59:51,265
No.

615
00:59:51,345 --> 00:59:53,305
Look carefully.

616
00:59:53,384 --> 00:59:56,904
Why do his nails, joints, and finger hair

617
00:59:56,984 --> 00:59:58,384
look familiar to me?

618
00:59:59,265 --> 01:00:02,464
These fingers definitely belong
to a handsome person.

619
01:00:02,545 --> 01:00:06,785
How are the fingers of a handsome man
and an ugly man different?

620
01:00:06,864 --> 01:00:07,705
Well…

621
01:00:08,225 --> 01:00:09,585
This means

622
01:00:09,665 --> 01:00:10,504
I am

623
01:00:10,585 --> 01:00:12,984
really damn handsome.

624
01:00:15,745 --> 01:00:17,105
Seriously?

625
01:00:17,185 --> 01:00:18,384
They are so different.

626
01:00:18,944 --> 01:00:20,145
Your fingers

627
01:00:20,225 --> 01:00:22,345
-are so tanned.
-Prib.

628
01:00:22,424 --> 01:00:23,265
Hey.

629
01:00:24,904 --> 01:00:27,904
Why is he covering his face with a book?

630
01:00:27,984 --> 01:00:28,944
I don't know.

631
01:00:29,024 --> 01:00:30,105
If I run into him,

632
01:00:30,185 --> 01:00:33,984
I'll ask him why he's trying
to hide his face.

633
01:00:34,065 --> 01:00:36,904
Instead of looking at his fingers,

634
01:00:36,984 --> 01:00:41,145
why don't you ask
his friends or relatives?

635
01:00:42,024 --> 01:00:45,625
Is it possible that he's an orphan?

636
01:00:45,705 --> 01:00:48,145
He's an orphan with relatives.

637
01:00:48,984 --> 01:00:49,825
I see.

638
01:00:50,625 --> 01:00:52,665
That's right.

639
01:00:52,745 --> 01:00:54,705
I'll ask his relatives.

640
01:00:54,785 --> 01:00:56,545
Please move.

641
01:00:57,105 --> 01:00:58,864
Aren't you going to work?

642
01:00:59,785 --> 01:01:00,785
Gosh.

643
01:01:01,625 --> 01:01:03,225
-Nut.
-Juea, hello.

644
01:01:03,305 --> 01:01:04,225
Hello.

645
01:01:04,305 --> 01:01:07,464
Can you give me
the location of the school?

646
01:01:07,545 --> 01:01:08,585
And the mall

647
01:01:08,665 --> 01:01:10,145
didn't give us their permission.

648
01:01:10,785 --> 01:01:13,665
-Okay.
-Let's talk inside. Come on.

649
01:01:14,545 --> 01:01:15,585
Wait.

650
01:01:18,145 --> 01:01:19,944
-Juea.
-Hold on.

651
01:01:24,185 --> 01:01:25,265
What are you doing?

652
01:01:30,384 --> 01:01:34,225
All men's hands look the same.
I shouldn't suspect anything.

653
01:01:34,825 --> 01:01:35,944
Come on, Nut.

654
01:01:36,464 --> 01:01:38,545
Okay, Prib. I'll send it to you.

655
01:01:38,625 --> 01:01:42,225
But I don't know how much
he knows about Tatarn.

656
01:01:42,305 --> 01:01:45,305
As far as I know,
their relationship wasn't going well.

657
01:01:45,384 --> 01:01:47,145
It's okay.

658
01:01:47,225 --> 01:01:49,265
It's worth a shot.

659
01:01:49,944 --> 01:01:51,464
Thank you, Mr. Anik.

660
01:01:51,944 --> 01:01:53,145
You're welcome.

661
01:01:54,065 --> 01:01:55,585
Let's go, Dad.

662
01:01:55,665 --> 01:01:56,825
Let's go.

663
01:01:56,904 --> 01:01:57,984
Where are we going?

664
01:01:58,065 --> 01:01:59,464
I've booked us a table.

665
01:01:59,545 --> 01:02:01,225
-Let's go.
-Yes.

666
01:02:09,745 --> 01:02:10,904
Yes, Lieutenant Kong.

667
01:02:12,384 --> 01:02:13,305
What?

668
01:02:20,265 --> 01:02:21,585
You can go to work.

669
01:02:21,665 --> 01:02:23,024
Don't worry about me.

670
01:02:23,105 --> 01:02:24,305
I can go with a friend.

671
01:02:25,984 --> 01:02:27,424
We can go next time.

672
01:02:27,504 --> 01:02:29,305
I'm coming back next week.

673
01:02:32,785 --> 01:02:34,464
Be honest with me.

674
01:02:35,305 --> 01:02:36,944
Are you so involved in this case

675
01:02:37,504 --> 01:02:38,785
because it's Neung's friend?

676
01:03:20,145 --> 01:03:21,265
Mister.

677
01:03:21,345 --> 01:03:22,185
Where are you?

678
01:03:22,265 --> 01:03:24,345
I'm at the hospital.

679
01:03:25,984 --> 01:03:26,944
What happened?

680
01:03:29,145 --> 01:03:30,424
I'm fine.

681
01:03:37,384 --> 01:03:38,785
Song.

682
01:03:38,864 --> 01:03:39,825
Song.

683
01:03:39,904 --> 01:03:40,745
Song.

684
01:03:42,984 --> 01:03:44,705
Why are you at the hospital then?

685
01:03:44,785 --> 01:03:47,944
I was selling an ad nearby,
so I came to visit my mom.

686
01:03:48,785 --> 01:03:50,105
Is something wrong?

687
01:03:56,384 --> 01:03:57,544
What's with you?

688
01:03:58,065 --> 01:04:00,065
I prepared you very well.

689
01:04:00,625 --> 01:04:02,305
How did this happen?

690
01:04:02,864 --> 01:04:04,384
What did you say to your dad?

691
01:04:06,705 --> 01:04:08,345
He ditched me for work

692
01:04:08,825 --> 01:04:10,665
before I could say anything.

693
01:04:11,305 --> 01:04:12,944
Don't be such a crybaby.

694
01:04:13,024 --> 01:04:14,384
Your dad is a cop.

695
01:04:14,464 --> 01:04:16,504
He had an urgent case.

696
01:04:17,504 --> 01:04:19,265
You've been his son for 18 years.

697
01:04:19,345 --> 01:04:20,984
You should get it by now.

698
01:04:22,145 --> 01:04:24,944
I wouldn't mind
if he went to work on another case.

699
01:04:26,105 --> 01:04:27,464
But the victim

700
01:04:27,544 --> 01:04:29,024
is Neung's friend.

701
01:04:29,825 --> 01:04:31,984
Neung always comes first for him.

702
01:04:34,305 --> 01:04:35,825
That's crazy.

703
01:04:35,904 --> 01:04:36,825
You think too much.

704
01:04:37,825 --> 01:04:39,065
It's true.

705
01:04:39,145 --> 01:04:40,705
Neung was his favorite

706
01:04:41,185 --> 01:04:42,745
ever since I was a baby.

707
01:04:44,585 --> 01:04:47,944
He was handsome, smart, athletic,

708
01:04:48,024 --> 01:04:51,544
into music, popular,
and good at everything.

709
01:04:53,705 --> 01:04:55,225
When Neung died,

710
01:04:56,105 --> 01:04:58,504
Dad's hope died along with him.

711
01:05:05,145 --> 01:05:06,864
I'm just someone

712
01:05:07,345 --> 01:05:08,944
he neglects.

713
01:05:10,024 --> 01:05:11,544
No matter how hard I try,

714
01:05:12,185 --> 01:05:14,265
I can only be Neung's shadow.

715
01:05:25,065 --> 01:05:26,585
All parents

716
01:05:27,904 --> 01:05:29,544
love their children the same way.

717
01:05:30,305 --> 01:05:31,464
That's not true.

718
01:05:33,024 --> 01:05:35,345
Maybe they love their children equally,

719
01:05:35,424 --> 01:05:37,625
but not in the same way.

720
01:05:42,024 --> 01:05:44,065
I'm sorry for eavesdropping.

721
01:05:44,145 --> 01:05:46,544
The conversation happens
to be about family,

722
01:05:46,625 --> 01:05:49,665
so I'm hoping to give you
my opinion as a mother.

723
01:05:56,424 --> 01:05:58,665
Parents can't love
their children the same way

724
01:05:59,225 --> 01:06:01,424
because every child is different.

725
01:06:01,504 --> 01:06:04,785
Some children who can take good care
of themselves

726
01:06:04,864 --> 01:06:07,225
may be neglected by their parents.

727
01:06:07,904 --> 01:06:11,105
But some children
who can't take care of themselves

728
01:06:11,864 --> 01:06:14,705
require more attention from the parents.

729
01:06:15,544 --> 01:06:17,544
Because parents treat them differently,

730
01:06:17,625 --> 01:06:20,745
children tend to think that parents
love their children unequally.

731
01:06:20,825 --> 01:06:22,504
The truth is

732
01:06:22,585 --> 01:06:26,105
they just love and care about
their children in different ways.

733
01:06:27,504 --> 01:06:28,345
That's right.

734
01:06:28,424 --> 01:06:29,745
I express my love

735
01:06:29,825 --> 01:06:32,105
towards my parents differently.

736
01:06:33,504 --> 01:06:34,864
But I love both of them.

737
01:06:36,785 --> 01:06:39,145
I talk to each of them

738
01:06:39,225 --> 01:06:41,145
about certain things.

739
01:06:45,785 --> 01:06:48,024
The fact that your father
gives you freedom

740
01:06:48,585 --> 01:06:51,384
doesn't mean he doesn't love
or care about you.

741
01:06:52,305 --> 01:06:55,265
It's because he trusts you.

742
01:06:57,544 --> 01:07:00,464
Your father has stuff he needs to work on,

743
01:07:01,265 --> 01:07:04,864
but you do too.

744
01:07:10,464 --> 01:07:11,745
You always

745
01:07:11,825 --> 01:07:14,424
compare yourself to your brother.

746
01:07:15,145 --> 01:07:16,504
You want to be as good as him,

747
01:07:17,464 --> 01:07:18,944
so your dad would praise you.

748
01:07:21,424 --> 01:07:23,265
You don't need to be like anyone.

749
01:07:24,305 --> 01:07:26,065
Just be yourself.

750
01:07:26,544 --> 01:07:28,424
You are second to none.

751
01:07:33,504 --> 01:07:34,544
Thank you

752
01:07:34,625 --> 01:07:36,585
for reminding me.

753
01:07:37,145 --> 01:07:38,424
You're welcome.

754
01:07:41,105 --> 01:07:42,384
Can I

755
01:07:43,065 --> 01:07:44,544
hug you?

756
01:07:45,145 --> 01:07:47,145
I don't have a mother to hug.

757
01:07:49,745 --> 01:07:50,625
Of course.

758
01:07:50,705 --> 01:07:51,944
Gen's friends

759
01:07:52,024 --> 01:07:54,225
are like my own children.

760
01:08:05,225 --> 01:08:06,424
That's enough.

761
01:08:06,504 --> 01:08:07,544
You sneaky punk.

762
01:08:08,384 --> 01:08:10,024
He's being protective of me.

763
01:08:16,865 --> 01:08:19,384
Mom, are you not coming home with me?

764
01:08:19,464 --> 01:08:23,305
-I'm not going back to the office.
-I have to meet two more patients.

765
01:08:23,384 --> 01:08:24,905
You can go home first.

766
01:08:26,305 --> 01:08:27,544
I'll see you at home.

767
01:08:27,624 --> 01:08:29,905
I need to check on my patients.

768
01:08:29,985 --> 01:08:32,905
Go home safely, both of you. See you.

769
01:08:39,945 --> 01:08:41,985
Mister, come have dinner with me.

770
01:08:42,065 --> 01:08:43,265
I've booked a table.

771
01:08:47,905 --> 01:08:49,145
Don't you have any friends

772
01:08:49,225 --> 01:08:50,504
other than me?

773
01:08:51,825 --> 01:08:54,464
You are not my friend.

774
01:08:54,544 --> 01:08:57,784
Please, come on. Have dinner with me.

775
01:08:58,624 --> 01:08:59,865
Please.

776
01:09:03,025 --> 01:09:03,945
Where is it?

777
01:09:09,905 --> 01:09:11,424
Wait, mister.

778
01:09:16,105 --> 01:09:20,305
Ms. Phone has fallen asleep
along with Ms. Sofa and Mr. Right Slipper.

779
01:09:21,664 --> 01:09:23,664
Mr. Rocking Chair looks sleepy too.

780
01:09:25,464 --> 01:09:27,265
Am I going to be next?

781
01:09:27,945 --> 01:09:29,185
Maybe

782
01:09:29,265 --> 01:09:32,345
only the furniture downstairs
is falling asleep.

783
01:09:32,424 --> 01:09:35,065
The rest of us upstairs are fine.

784
01:09:35,744 --> 01:09:39,025
But Mr. Right Slipper
followed Mrs. Na around the house.

785
01:09:39,105 --> 01:09:41,065
He still fell asleep.

786
01:09:41,145 --> 01:09:43,305
Teddy goes around the house too,

787
01:09:43,384 --> 01:09:45,865
so he might fall asleep next.

788
01:09:45,945 --> 01:09:48,945
We don't know why the furniture
is falling asleep.

789
01:09:49,025 --> 01:09:51,664
And you don't know how you became a human.

790
01:09:52,145 --> 01:09:54,784
I don't know if those two things
are related,

791
01:09:54,865 --> 01:09:57,945
but you might be the only one
who can find the answer.

792
01:09:58,025 --> 01:10:02,225
If you discover where you came from,

793
01:10:02,305 --> 01:10:06,945
you might find a way to stay awake,
unlike the others.

794
01:10:07,025 --> 01:10:08,945
Did you find any more clues yesterday?

795
01:10:09,425 --> 01:10:10,545
Yes.

796
01:10:11,225 --> 01:10:13,065
Yesterday, Prib said…

797
01:10:13,945 --> 01:10:16,865
She said it was a tall male student.

798
01:10:19,425 --> 01:10:21,145
After he bought me,

799
01:10:21,744 --> 01:10:23,265
he put a bandana on me.

800
01:10:24,664 --> 01:10:25,784
Excuse me.

801
01:10:25,865 --> 01:10:27,784
I'll take these two items

802
01:10:27,865 --> 01:10:31,425
and please swap the bow
for this pink bandana.

803
01:10:31,985 --> 01:10:33,425
Don't you like the bow?

804
01:10:33,505 --> 01:10:36,624
I want it to be special.

805
01:10:37,145 --> 01:10:38,784
Plus, he likes the color pink.

806
01:10:38,865 --> 01:10:40,505
-All right.
-Thank you.

807
01:10:42,985 --> 01:10:45,664
You hid the teddy's scarf
in my room, didn't you?

808
01:10:46,825 --> 01:10:47,865
Didn't you?

809
01:10:48,744 --> 01:10:50,065
I didn't.

810
01:10:51,945 --> 01:10:53,744
It had fallen, so I put it away.

811
01:10:53,825 --> 01:10:54,985
Don't lie!

812
01:10:55,545 --> 01:10:57,985
You were going through my personal stuff!

813
01:10:58,065 --> 01:10:59,624
What do you want?

814
01:11:00,305 --> 01:11:02,025
The scarf. The book.

815
01:11:02,784 --> 01:11:04,585
Still think it's unrelated?

816
01:11:07,385 --> 01:11:08,465
Could it be…

817
01:11:14,985 --> 01:11:17,624
BE WITH YOU

818
01:11:17,704 --> 01:11:22,185
BE WITH YOU

819
01:11:37,265 --> 01:11:38,465
You're home early.

820
01:11:38,545 --> 01:11:40,105
Yes.

821
01:11:40,185 --> 01:11:42,225
I talked to Juea and had a meeting.

822
01:11:42,305 --> 01:11:44,385
I have to write more scenes.

823
01:11:44,465 --> 01:11:46,225
I'm pulling an all-nighter tonight.

824
01:11:50,744 --> 01:11:52,704
He's writing about his life.

825
01:11:53,185 --> 01:11:55,265
Even if it's a little sad,

826
01:11:55,744 --> 01:11:57,185
that's okay,

827
01:11:57,265 --> 01:12:00,585
because I'll add sweetness to his life,

828
01:12:03,825 --> 01:12:04,784
There might be clues

829
01:12:05,345 --> 01:12:07,345
about that man in the screenplay.

830
01:12:07,985 --> 01:12:09,385
Then you should get writing.

831
01:12:12,265 --> 01:12:13,145
What's with you?

832
01:12:14,145 --> 01:12:15,465
You usually tell me to rest.

833
01:12:16,664 --> 01:12:17,624
Well,

834
01:12:17,704 --> 01:12:19,425
finish it so you can rest.

835
01:12:19,985 --> 01:12:21,385
Keep on writing.

836
01:12:21,465 --> 01:12:22,825
I'll give you a massage.

837
01:12:25,345 --> 01:12:26,664
You're being weird today.

838
01:12:29,145 --> 01:12:30,545
I might be weird,

839
01:12:31,105 --> 01:12:32,784
but I look cute every day.

