846
01:13:19,145 --> 01:13:20,345
That must be Nut.

847
01:13:40,225 --> 01:13:41,345
Song

848
01:13:41,425 --> 01:13:42,664
plays Nont,

849
01:13:42,744 --> 01:13:46,065
the popular basketball player
whom Nut had a crush on.

850
01:13:46,145 --> 01:13:47,425
He didn't like Nut back.

851
01:13:48,305 --> 01:13:49,985
He's probably

852
01:13:51,345 --> 01:13:52,305
Neung,

853
01:13:52,865 --> 01:13:54,305
Song's brother.

854
01:14:48,945 --> 01:14:51,185
The character Tonnam

855
01:14:51,265 --> 01:14:53,145
is Nont's best friend.

856
01:14:58,664 --> 01:15:00,265
Wow, that's beautiful.

857
01:15:01,105 --> 01:15:02,145
Thank you.

858
01:15:06,865 --> 01:15:08,225
Tonnam

859
01:15:08,305 --> 01:15:09,905
is a young and confident thinker

860
01:15:09,985 --> 01:15:12,664
who loves to read

861
01:15:13,145 --> 01:15:14,704
and is obsessed with art.

862
01:15:16,025 --> 01:15:17,945
There's only one moon.

863
01:15:18,664 --> 01:15:19,664
Right?

864
01:15:21,505 --> 01:15:23,345
How about I draw another moon?

865
01:15:25,025 --> 01:15:26,784
If you draw another moon,

866
01:15:27,505 --> 01:15:29,865
the first moon will lose its meaning.

867
01:16:21,704 --> 01:16:22,545
TONNAM

868
01:17:28,744 --> 01:17:29,704
Tarn.

869
01:17:30,664 --> 01:17:32,824
Why would you do that?

870
01:17:32,905 --> 01:17:33,824
Why?

871
01:17:33,905 --> 01:17:35,744
-Tarn.
-It's funny.

872
01:17:35,824 --> 01:17:37,624
That hurts.

873
01:17:38,105 --> 01:17:40,505
-My ear hurts.
-Did your ear explode?

874
01:18:06,624 --> 01:18:08,265
This "T" guy

875
01:18:08,345 --> 01:18:09,905
is definitely portrayed by Tonnam.

876
01:18:11,225 --> 01:18:14,305
I need to find the person
the character Tonnam is based on.

877
01:18:33,865 --> 01:18:37,784
BASKETBALL TEAM BATCH 128

878
01:18:47,545 --> 01:18:48,784
What are you doing?

879
01:19:00,185 --> 01:19:01,145
You…

880
01:19:06,945 --> 01:19:08,425
Ma'am.

881
01:19:09,145 --> 01:19:10,025
Ma'am.

882
01:19:10,585 --> 01:19:11,905
Are you okay?

883
01:19:23,624 --> 01:19:24,664
Ma'am.

884
01:19:24,744 --> 01:19:25,704
Anont.

885
01:19:27,784 --> 01:19:30,425
Are you still wandering here?

886
01:19:30,505 --> 01:19:32,425
You should go to the light.

887
01:19:32,505 --> 01:19:34,385
I'll make merit for you.

888
01:19:34,865 --> 01:19:38,265
-Ma'am, I'm human.
-No…

889
01:19:41,385 --> 01:19:43,865
You've been dead for ten years.

890
01:19:43,945 --> 01:19:45,824
Don't you know?

891
01:19:48,744 --> 01:19:49,985
Sathu.

892
01:19:50,065 --> 01:19:53,345
Ma'am, my name is Tofu, not Anont.

893
01:19:53,425 --> 01:19:55,185
I'm here to shoot the series.

894
01:20:02,985 --> 01:20:04,185
Really?

895
01:20:05,624 --> 01:20:07,105
Are you really human?

896
01:20:07,185 --> 01:20:08,345
Yes.

897
01:20:13,265 --> 01:20:14,905
My heart almost stopped.

898
01:20:16,105 --> 01:20:16,945
Listen.

899
01:20:17,505 --> 01:20:18,865
Peeranut told me

900
01:20:19,824 --> 01:20:22,744
that the script
is based on his experience.

901
01:20:23,664 --> 01:20:25,345
I never thought

902
01:20:25,425 --> 01:20:29,824
he would find an actor
who looked so similar to his senior.

903
01:20:31,465 --> 01:20:33,145
Do you know Nut?

904
01:20:33,824 --> 01:20:34,824
Of course.

905
01:20:35,305 --> 01:20:36,545
Look.

906
01:20:36,624 --> 01:20:38,744
I even know his parents,

907
01:20:38,824 --> 01:20:41,624
let alone him.

908
01:20:42,265 --> 01:20:43,624
I was afraid

909
01:20:44,105 --> 01:20:48,105
his puppy love was going to stop him
from graduating.

910
01:20:49,624 --> 01:20:51,425
Why? What happened?

911
01:20:51,985 --> 01:20:53,585
He got a boyfriend.

912
01:20:53,664 --> 01:20:56,385
Luckily, I stopped him in time.

913
01:20:57,465 --> 01:20:59,225
Do you know his boyfriend?

914
01:21:00,065 --> 01:21:01,065
Look.

915
01:21:01,145 --> 01:21:04,265
I took care of Peeranut
as if he was my own son.

916
01:21:04,345 --> 01:21:05,824
-What was his name?
-I…

917
01:21:06,385 --> 01:21:07,784
He was Anont's best friend.

918
01:21:07,865 --> 01:21:09,624
-His name was--
-Tofu.

919
01:21:11,065 --> 01:21:12,385
You're here.

920
01:21:18,265 --> 01:21:19,145
My goodness.

921
01:21:19,624 --> 01:21:21,505
You interrupted our conversation.

922
01:21:21,585 --> 01:21:23,465
Were you afraid I would say something?

923
01:21:24,145 --> 01:21:25,305
No.

924
01:21:26,145 --> 01:21:28,265
I just hate it when people talk
behind my back,

925
01:21:28,345 --> 01:21:29,624
the way they used to.

926
01:21:30,225 --> 01:21:31,185
Listen.

927
01:21:31,265 --> 01:21:34,865
If that's your way
of calling me a busybody,

928
01:21:34,945 --> 01:21:37,265
you should know that I meant well.

929
01:21:38,664 --> 01:21:39,624
Are you sure

930
01:21:40,624 --> 01:21:42,465
it wasn't for your own benefit?

931
01:21:43,025 --> 01:21:44,105
Peeranut.

932
01:21:45,905 --> 01:21:49,185
If you think badly of my goodwill,

933
01:21:49,265 --> 01:21:51,265
I want you to think again.

934
01:21:51,824 --> 01:21:55,065
You should realize
that you grew up with a good life

935
01:21:55,145 --> 01:21:58,784
because I pulled you back on track.

936
01:21:59,505 --> 01:22:00,545
Yes.

937
01:22:01,545 --> 01:22:03,145
You are partly the reason

938
01:22:03,905 --> 01:22:05,225
my life is like this.

939
01:22:07,545 --> 01:22:08,784
Thank you so much.

940
01:22:10,784 --> 01:22:11,945
Let's go, Tofu.

941
01:22:20,664 --> 01:22:21,704
Nut.

942
01:22:23,225 --> 01:22:24,704
Why did you go back to the club?

943
01:22:25,905 --> 01:22:27,265
I forgot my phone.

944
01:22:28,425 --> 01:22:30,345
What did she say to you?

945
01:22:30,905 --> 01:22:32,305
Nothing much.

946
01:22:32,385 --> 01:22:34,225
She asked why I look like Neung.

947
01:22:39,465 --> 01:22:41,145
Don't listen

948
01:22:41,225 --> 01:22:42,624
to anything she says.

949
01:22:45,545 --> 01:22:47,624
She's a dictator

950
01:22:48,425 --> 01:22:50,145
who thinks she's always right.

951
01:22:55,465 --> 01:22:57,185
Go back to the shoot first.

952
01:22:57,265 --> 01:22:58,624
I'm going to the toilet.

953
01:23:12,465 --> 01:23:15,624
It's okay. I'll ask Song myself.

954
01:23:22,345 --> 01:23:23,385
Sir.

955
01:23:24,985 --> 01:23:27,425
Song told me
he was shooting his series here.

956
01:23:27,905 --> 01:23:29,385
Hey.

957
01:23:29,465 --> 01:23:30,585
Can I ask you something?

958
01:23:31,425 --> 01:23:34,145
Has Song complained
or come to you for advice?

959
01:23:37,265 --> 01:23:38,664
No.

960
01:23:39,225 --> 01:23:41,105
Song is a talented guy.

961
01:23:41,185 --> 01:23:43,185
He's my hero.

962
01:23:43,265 --> 01:23:46,345
If someone were to ask for advice,
it would be me.

963
01:23:46,425 --> 01:23:49,784
Song used to call Neung his hero.

964
01:23:50,305 --> 01:23:53,545
Today, someone who looks like Neung
is calling Song a hero.

965
01:23:54,065 --> 01:23:55,784
It's a little weird to me.

966
01:23:57,265 --> 01:23:59,265
But Song is really my hero.

967
01:24:00,145 --> 01:24:01,824
Think about it.

968
01:24:01,905 --> 01:24:03,505
How can someone be handsome,

969
01:24:03,585 --> 01:24:04,545
hardworking,

970
01:24:04,624 --> 01:24:06,225
smart,

971
01:24:06,305 --> 01:24:07,824
talented,

972
01:24:07,905 --> 01:24:08,985
good at basketball,

973
01:24:09,545 --> 01:24:10,865
and good at riding a bike?

974
01:24:10,945 --> 01:24:12,345
He's good at everything.

975
01:24:13,385 --> 01:24:14,545
Is that so?

976
01:24:16,945 --> 01:24:19,345
You might not realize how talented Song is

977
01:24:20,744 --> 01:24:23,265
because you're busy
thinking about your dead child.

978
01:24:25,545 --> 01:24:27,744
Maybe you're neglecting
the child you have left.

979
01:24:32,425 --> 01:24:34,704
What part of your life
don't I take an interest in?

980
01:24:35,225 --> 01:24:36,624
There's a lot.

981
01:24:36,704 --> 01:24:38,744
You don't remember the food I like.

982
01:24:38,824 --> 01:24:41,185
You don't even remember my birthday.

983
01:24:41,265 --> 01:24:43,905
I wasn't the one who gave birth to you.

984
01:24:44,985 --> 01:24:47,185
But you always remember Neung's birthday.

985
01:24:47,824 --> 01:24:50,704
Even after he passed away,
you still remember.

986
01:24:54,704 --> 01:24:56,945
Song never told me anything.

987
01:24:58,865 --> 01:25:00,465
He's a strong person.

988
01:25:02,664 --> 01:25:04,225
But every strong person

989
01:25:05,105 --> 01:25:07,265
can get weak sometimes.

990
01:25:10,345 --> 01:25:12,185
I'm a terrible father.

991
01:25:14,465 --> 01:25:15,425
No.

992
01:25:16,545 --> 01:25:18,465
No one's perfect.

993
01:25:19,784 --> 01:25:21,385
And it's not wrong

994
01:25:22,065 --> 01:25:24,905
to mourn and miss your dead child.

995
01:25:25,905 --> 01:25:28,985
However, you can't neglect
the child you have left.

996
01:25:31,744 --> 01:25:34,465
To be forgotten while you are still alive

997
01:25:35,505 --> 01:25:38,105
hurts more than being separated by death.

998
01:25:45,145 --> 01:25:46,065
Thank you.

999
01:25:46,664 --> 01:25:49,664
Study hard and take care of the club.

1000
01:26:05,185 --> 01:26:06,225
Put this on me.

1001
01:26:16,865 --> 01:26:18,704
Now, we have one each.

1002
01:26:27,624 --> 01:26:28,945
That's it for today.

1003
01:26:39,265 --> 01:26:41,265
-Thank you so much.
-The shoot is over.

1004
01:26:42,985 --> 01:26:47,624
I said, the shoot is over.
Girls, the shoot is over.

1005
01:26:53,744 --> 01:26:55,065
Congratulations.

1006
01:26:56,145 --> 01:26:57,744
The shoot will be done soon.

1007
01:26:57,824 --> 01:26:59,624
Does this mean I won't see you anymore?

1008
01:27:00,345 --> 01:27:01,425
Yes.

1009
01:27:01,505 --> 01:27:04,505
We're going separate ways.

1010
01:27:05,585 --> 01:27:08,065
Can I live at your house then?

1011
01:27:08,624 --> 01:27:10,465
My dad will ask for your hand.

1012
01:27:10,545 --> 01:27:14,065
Jeez, as soon as your stress goes away,
you're here to annoy me.

1013
01:27:14,905 --> 01:27:16,145
Have you talked to him?

1014
01:27:20,025 --> 01:27:21,025
Not yet.

1015
01:27:22,305 --> 01:27:23,545
What are you waiting for?

1016
01:27:23,624 --> 01:27:24,864
Shall I talk to him?

1017
01:27:26,824 --> 01:27:29,345
How will you introduce yourself to him?

1018
01:27:32,265 --> 01:27:33,145
Well…

1019
01:27:33,744 --> 01:27:36,265
I'll say I'm a senior who pities you.

1020
01:27:39,225 --> 01:27:41,465
Have you heard of the phrase

1021
01:27:41,545 --> 01:27:44,864
"Pity is the foundation of love"?

1022
01:27:46,305 --> 01:27:47,545
No.

1023
01:27:47,624 --> 01:27:49,185
I've only heard of sympathy.

1024
01:28:01,145 --> 01:28:02,505
I wasn't expecting you.

1025
01:28:05,305 --> 01:28:06,545
I came to support you.

1026
01:28:08,305 --> 01:28:10,905
You've invited me many times,
but I never came.

1027
01:28:12,265 --> 01:28:13,824
You didn't tell me

1028
01:28:13,905 --> 01:28:15,465
it was a love story.

1029
01:28:18,905 --> 01:28:20,185
You don't mind, do you?

1030
01:28:21,784 --> 01:28:23,065
Of course not.

1031
01:28:23,145 --> 01:28:24,345
It's just acting.

1032
01:28:26,385 --> 01:28:27,824
You're not really gay.

1033
01:28:30,545 --> 01:28:31,824
Are you?

1034
01:28:36,385 --> 01:28:37,265
Song.

1035
01:28:38,185 --> 01:28:39,664
I'm sorry.

1036
01:28:41,744 --> 01:28:43,265
I keep breaking my promises.

1037
01:28:44,105 --> 01:28:46,265
I flew here as soon as I finished working.

1038
01:28:48,465 --> 01:28:50,465
Dad, don't worry.

1039
01:28:51,065 --> 01:28:52,945
I know you are busy.

1040
01:28:57,065 --> 01:28:57,945
Song.

1041
01:28:59,025 --> 01:29:00,545
I'm not working hard

1042
01:29:02,265 --> 01:29:04,265
because the victim is Neung's friend.

1043
01:29:04,345 --> 01:29:06,425
I would do the same with any case.

1044
01:29:09,345 --> 01:29:11,025
I'm sorry

1045
01:29:12,065 --> 01:29:13,225
if I hurt your feelings.

1046
01:29:18,744 --> 01:29:19,704
In the past,

1047
01:29:19,784 --> 01:29:22,065
I've neglected you

1048
01:29:23,385 --> 01:29:25,505
because I knew you could
take care of yourself.

1049
01:29:26,744 --> 01:29:28,425
But the truth is, deep down,

1050
01:29:29,065 --> 01:29:30,505
you're still a puppy

1051
01:29:31,465 --> 01:29:33,265
who needs his daddy, aren't you?

1052
01:29:43,585 --> 01:29:45,225
I will try

1053
01:29:46,145 --> 01:29:47,545
to be here for you more.

1054
01:29:55,545 --> 01:29:57,025
I'm sorry.

1055
01:29:58,545 --> 01:30:02,864
It's my fault
for never telling you how I feel.

1056
01:30:07,784 --> 01:30:09,305
We are going

1057
01:30:10,585 --> 01:30:12,545
to be honest with each other

1058
01:30:13,425 --> 01:30:15,985
to avoid any misunderstandings
in the future.

1059
01:30:19,664 --> 01:30:21,545
We only have each other.

1060
01:30:22,585 --> 01:30:24,225
You are my life and soul.

1061
01:30:29,585 --> 01:30:30,905
I love you.

1062
01:30:32,025 --> 01:30:33,385
I love you too.

1063
01:30:52,744 --> 01:30:54,025
Come on.

1064
01:30:54,105 --> 01:30:55,505
Let's give them some privacy.

1065
01:30:56,784 --> 01:30:57,824
Tofu.

1066
01:30:57,905 --> 01:30:59,505
Go get changed.

1067
01:30:59,585 --> 01:31:01,105
I'll wait in the car.

1068
01:31:01,185 --> 01:31:02,345
Okay.

1069
01:31:09,545 --> 01:31:10,385
Sometimes,

1070
01:31:10,465 --> 01:31:13,065
we forget that we are still breathing.

1071
01:31:14,624 --> 01:31:15,864
But it doesn't mean

1072
01:31:16,465 --> 01:31:17,985
that breathing isn't important,

1073
01:31:18,945 --> 01:31:19,985
does it?

1074
01:31:27,664 --> 01:31:29,265
Do you want to be gay?

1075
01:31:29,824 --> 01:31:31,305
Don't you want to be a man?

1076
01:31:31,385 --> 01:31:33,265
Are you and Nut in love?

1077
01:31:34,824 --> 01:31:35,824
Yes.

1078
01:31:39,345 --> 01:31:41,105
You can hate me all you want.

1079
01:31:42,145 --> 01:31:44,585
But I will never be who you want me to be.

1080
01:31:44,664 --> 01:31:46,945
Did your ex-boyfriend traumatize you

1081
01:31:47,545 --> 01:31:48,744
from dating a younger man?

1082
01:31:50,425 --> 01:31:53,704
Not all younger men are the same.
Don't generalize us.

1083
01:31:54,505 --> 01:31:56,345
Don't you have confidence in me

1084
01:31:57,505 --> 01:31:59,185
when I'm with you at all?

1085
01:33:07,824 --> 01:33:12,824
Subtitle translation by:
Pet-chompoo Sa-ngarmangkang
